      "comment": "ZIPPING CHEBET (1) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.3 lengths at this track in a handy 29.92 beating Jimmy Jams. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. The hardest to beat again. TERRA BELLA (7) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (19.26) last time in a Grade 5 at Q Straight. Expected to run well. HARA'S NERO (3) jumped from a squeeze box last start but was quickly into stride and led throughout to score (30.23) at this track in a Grade 6 over 520m. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Will go close again if runs up to latest. ADA TANGO (2) was unplaced here last start but gets her chance to atone.",
